g.text: Grandpa, I was able to create graphs of the ocean temperatures and sardine landings for the years 1915-1968 for the peak spawning months. Do you see any trend or pattern from the graphs?
That's true. I think I need to see if there is a real trend in the data by somehow smoothing out the curve.

I'm not seeing anything at all in these two graphs! The data has a lot of noise in both graphs which is making it difficult to see if the ocean temperatures and sardine landings are increasing or decreasing over the years.

Did you say, smooth? That's what I'm all about, using my smooth statistics skills to make sense of the data! It looks like a smoothing technique called the loess line would work for these two datasets.
